oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Pre-Civil War bank notes
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Four pre-Civil War bank notes include two $50 notes from the Commercial Bank of Alabama in Selma, one $50 note from the Bank of Chattanooga, and a $20 note from the Bank of the State of Georgia. They were found in a leather pocketbook (wallet). [See item wmca084.]
